.TH IMGMOD-PNG8 1 "July 7, 2026" "imgmod 1.3.0"
.SH NAME
imgmod-png8 \- Convert an image to PNG8
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B imgmod png8
[\fB-h\fR] \fIINPUT\fR [\fIOUTPUT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B imgmod png8
uses ImageMagick to write an image as PNG8.

When \fIOUTPUT\fR is omitted, the output path is generated from \fIINPUT\fR as
\fISTEM\fB-png8.png\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Show usage help.
.TP
.B \-v, --version
Show the plugin name and version.
.SH OUTPUT
The command prints the output file path and reports it through
\fBimgmod_output\fR so it can be optimized by \fBimgmod -o\fR.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B magick
ImageMagick command used to transform the image.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR imgmod (1)
